<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7304> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7304" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Monetalis. In MRR 2.437, and Index, 557, refer also to Crawford RRC 1.249-250, 151 B.C. Crawford would identify this Sulla as either a brother of the dictator's father or a son of the praetor of 186 (384) and grandfather of the dictator, according to the method of counting the generations intended in Veil. 2.17.2, where the dictator is described as sextus a Cornelio Rufino (RE no. 302, Cos. 290 and 277).\n" .
